Explanation:

The provided solution implements a Trie data structure in Java. The Trie is built by iterating over the characters of the input string. Each character is processed, and if the character is not found in the trie, a new node is created at that position. The search operation checks if the current node is the end of a word by checking if it is the last character of the string. The startsWith operation is similar to the search operation but checks if the prefix is a substring of the trie. The energy implications are low because the operations are constant time operations, and the space complexity is O(n) due to storing the characters and their corresponding nodes in the trie.

